A fictional female character from the [[Gundam]] series. She first appeared in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] from 1979.

[spoiler]Lalah was forced to work in an Indian brothel in her youth, but was rescued by Char Aznable to whom she is fiercely loyal and forever in debt. She later becomes a very dangerous newtype [[Zeon]] ace pilot in her own right. Her [[mecha]] of choice is the [[Elmeth]]. 

Lalah tragically dies during a pivotal [[space]] [[battle]], accidentaly killed by an unwilling Amuro while defending her savior and protector Char. This event would haunt both Amuro and Char for the rest of their lives.

In the SD Gundam skits, she is shown having the business end of a beam saber for a bindi.[/spoiler]

title: bayberry
body:
Waxberry (Morella rubra Lour.), a evergreen tree species in the Myricaceae family, has a neat, spherical crown; its branches are fragile and easily breakable. The leaves are leathery, alternate, lanceolate or ovate in shape; the plants are dioecious or occasionally monoecious. Female flowers are in soft racemes, bright red and thread-like; the fruit is a spherical drupe with nipple-like protrusions on the outer surface, coming in red, purple, white, pink, and other colors. The flowering season is in April, and the fruiting season is from June to July.

Waxberry is native to Sanqi Market, Yao City, Ningbo City, Zhejiang Province, China. The Shiao Site has the earliest and most accurate remains of the waxberry tree in China, dating back to 2520 BC, which is over 4500 years ago.

title: conte_di_cavour_nuovo_(kancolle)
body:
The second remodel of [[Conte di Cavour (kancolle)|]] from [[Kantai Collection]], released at the same time as her debut in the Kancolle 2021 Summer Event in August 2021.

The main difference between the base form and the remodel is that the remodel's dress doesn't have sleeves.

This is a hypothetical remodel based on plans to modernize her following heavy damage incurred in the Battle of Taranto that went unfinished at the time of the Armistice of Cassibile in September 1943. The superfiring 320 mm turrets were to have carried two-step platforms for additional AA weapons (work was already done by summer 1943); the 120 mm turrets, while not removed, were to have been modified to receive the new 135 mm dual purpose twin mounts, and an additional Gufo radar installed on the foremast.

title: kongou_kai_ni_(kancolle)
body:
The second and third remodels of [[Kantai Collection]]'s [[Kongou (kancolle)|]].

For her second remodeling, this new form revamps her costume and rig and modifies her hairband (the "wings" are now [[radar]]s, the band itself is now fully gold/brass instead of a gold/brass and black pattern). This is the most obvious change if she is not depicted with her rigging as her [[nontraditional miko]] outfit remains unchanged. 

More than 5 years later, she obtained her third remodel, termed Kai Ni C (or Hei). This form revamps her costume and rig further and takes advantage of Konishi's art style evolution as well as given cues from other Konishi ships. The most notable features are her boots (similar to the Shoukaku-class Kai Ni), her headband (more intricate), her jacket (now collared) and sleeves (back to being attached to her top) as well as her rig (more detailed for the HD/HTML5 era and features some [[torpedo tubes]]).

title: conquest_end
body:
The [[bad end]] in [[Choujigen Game Neptune Mk2]], known as the Conquest Ending.

[spoiler]The CPUs find that the only way to defeat the revived Deity of Sin [[Magiquone]]/Arfoire is to use [[gehaburn|an evil sword]] which grows in power when it kills one of CPU lineage. [[Noire (neptunia)|]], [[uni (neptunia)|Uni]], [[Blanc (neptunia)|]], [[rom (neptunia)|Rom]], [[ram (neptunia)|Ram]], [[Vert (neptunia)|]] and [[neptune (neptunia)|Neptune]] all reluctantly sacrifice their own lives so [[Nepgear]] can use the sword and save Gamindustri. She defeats Magiquone/Arfoire, but the latter taunts her that a world with only one CPU - without strife, without contest - will eventually stagnate and rot, and when that happens, she will return.[/spoiler]

The remake, Hyperdimension Neptunia Re;Birth 2: Sisters Generation features an alternate "good" version called the Holy Sword Ending, which splits from the Conquest Ending partway through and leads to a [[good end]].

[spoiler]In [[Nepnep Connect: Chaos Chanpuru]], an alternate version of Nepgear, named [[Purple Sister V]], was introduced, who is heavily implied to be a future version of Nepgear from this route.[/spoiler]

title: leo_minor_(constellation)
body:
Leo Minor (the [[cub|Lesser]] [[Lion]]) is a small [[constellation]] located in the Northern celestial hemisphere. Its brightest star is Praecipua.

Leo Minor usually represents 3-4 connected stars, with two main ("body") lines forming an obtuse angle, sometimes with a third straight line added. In some cases, a fifth star is added below the "body", making it a quadrilateral. The constellation lies directly above its "parent" [[Leo (constellation)|]] (the Lion) and below [[Ursa Major (constellation)|]] (the Great Bear).

title: transformers:_generation_1
body:
[quote][i]"ROBOTS IN DISGUISE...!!!"[/i] - Official slogan.[/quote]

The original 1984 [[Transformers]] toyline and cartoon series, retroactively referred to as Generation 1 (or G1) after the Generation 2 toyline's release. The series consists of 4 TV seasons with a theatrical film set at the midpoint, as well as two companion comic runs by [[Marvel]] - one produced in the US, and the other in the UK. 

The G1 TV cartoon is notable because it was made in an 80s [[mecha]] anime style. The [[box art]] for the [[toy]]s based on the cartoon was made by [[Jeffrey Mangiat]]. For art done in his style see [[Jeffrey Mangiat (style)]]. The [[Marvel]] [[comic]]s company also contributed to the original franchise by developing the whole fictional Generation 1 universe of the TV series and its robot characters info and backgrounds, all created by Marvel comics writer "Bob Budiansky":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Budiansky. 

The [b]Transformers: Generation 1[/b] tag is for the original series and supplementary media only. In [[Japan]], the G1 continuity lasted much longer and encompassed several non-G1 series in its framework; on Danbooru G1 follows the original G1 continuity, so the several direct sequels G1 received that are exclusive to Japan are not covered under this tag. For those series see the following tags:
* [[Transformers: The Headmasters]]
* [[Transformers Super-God Masterforce]]
* [[Transformers Victory]]
* [[Transformers Zone]]
* [[Transformers: Return of Convoy]]
* [[Transformers Operation Combination]]
* [[Kiss Players]]

title: street_gutter
body:
[[drain_(object)|Drainage]] ditches dug alongside a [[street]], generally lined in concrete or another paving material.

In Japan these often are covered by a series of concrete slabs with slots between them to both allow drainage and act as handles to remove the slabs for repair or cleaning (see post #3081063). The drainage ditch can also be covered by long metal grates as in post #575226.  These are usually placed between the roadway and a sidewalk, or create a sidewalk on their own.

For intermittent grates or gaps in a curbside that lead to a deeper underground sewer system, instead use [[storm drain]].

h4. See also

title: wild_arms_1
body:
The first game in the [[Wild Arms]] series, encompassing both the original PS1 release and its remake Wild Arms: Alter Code F.

Taking place in the fantasy world of Filgaia, Wild Arms follows the adventures of a band of miscreants and adventurers called Dream Chasers who scour the world in search of excitement and fortune. The player assumes control of a young boy named Rudy who has the ability to operate powerful weapons called Ancient Relic Machines (ARMs), forbidden remnants of a lost age that resemble guns. Along with his companions Jack and Cecilia, the group must use their respective skills to navigate through the vast wastelands and dungeons of Filgaia and prevent an otherworldly threat from reviving their lost leader and destroying the world. -- Wikipedia

The PS1 Wild Arms started the series' recurring idea of steampunk, spaghetti western-styled worlds and characters blended together with typical fantasy world ideas like magic and summonable deities. In addition, both Wild Arms games are lauded for their storylines and characterization.

The PS1 version only has three playable characters:

* [[Rody Roughnight]]
* [[Jack Van Burace]]
* [[Cecilia Lynne Adelhyde]]

The PS2 version adds four new PCs who were all present in the original as NPCs.

* [[Jane Maxwell]], aka Calamity Jane
* [[Magdalen Harts]]
* [[Emma Hetfield]]
* [[Zed (wild arms)|]]

title: covid-19_test
body:
A COVID-19 Rapid Diagnostic Test, a simple testing device similar to a [[pregnancy test]]. 

They're a lateral flow test used to determine either COVID-19 antigens for a current infection or COVID-19 antibodies for having had a past infection.  The antigen test features marks for C and T, where a single line on the C indicates negative for infection, while a line at both C and T indicates a positive for infection.  The antibody test features the marks C, IgG, and IgM or C, G, and M.  Having a line at the IgG or IgM mark indicates the presence of antibodies and having had a past infection.

title: welrod
body:
The [b]Welrod[/b] is a World War II-era [[bolt action]] [[handgun]] with an integrated [[suppressor]] of British origin. It was designed by Major Hugh Reeves at the Inter-Services Research Bureau  near [b]Wel[/b]wyn Garden City, which gave the Welrod its name, as well as "rod" for being a gangland slang for [[gun]].

The Welrod is visually recognizable by its roughly tonfa-like shape thanks to its long tubular suppressor, L-shaped trigger and a long bulging trigger guard (while Mk II variant lacks it).

title: quick_time_event
body:
In video games, a Quick Time Event (QTE) is a method of context-sensitive gameplay in which the player performs actions on the control device shortly after the appearance of an on-screen prompt. It allows for limited control of the game character during cut scenes or cinematic sequences in the game. Failing these segments, either by failing to take the correct action in time, performing a different action, or taking no action at all takes the scene in a different course/ending.

The [B]NKVD[/B] (Russian: Наро́дный комиссариа́т вну́тренних дел, [People's Commissariat for Internal Affairs]) was the interior ministry of the [[soviet|Soviet Union]], established in 1917. title: daisy
body:
Daisy and aster are blanket names for many similar looking [[flower|flowers]] in the expansive [i]Asteraceae[/i] family. Asters are practically indistinguishable from daisies for tagging purposes.

Daisies and asters typically have a spiky-looking head made up of tiny disc florets surrounded by a multitude of long petals. Gerber daisies will also have an inner ring of ray florets around the center head.

Common daisy colors include white petals with a yellow or orange center and yellow petals with a dark brown center, but daisies & asters can come in practically [b]any[/b] color.

For tagging purposes, limit this tag to flowers that look generally like a Common Daisy, a Black-Eyed Susan, a Gerber Daisy, asters, or any color variation on that basic design.

h4. Other distinctive flowers in [i]Asteraceae[/i]

* [[Chamomile]]
* [[Chicory (flower)|]]
* [[Chrysanthemum]]
* [[Cornflower]]
* [[Cosmos (flower)|]]

title: little_witch_academia
body:
[b]Little Witch Academia[/b] is a 2013 animated short produced by [i][[Trigger (company)|]][/i] for [i]Anime Mirai 2013[/i]. The short was created and directed by [[Yoshinari You]] and written by Ootsuka Masahiko and was released in theaters on March 2, 2013. [i]Trigger[/i] later began streaming the short with English subtitles on YouTube from April 19, 2013.

On July 5, 2013, Trigger announced at [[Anime Expo]] that a new episode, tentatively titled [i][b]Little Witch Academia 2[/b][/i], would be developed in response to the reception the first episode received. The project will begin production in late 2013 following the airing of [[Kill la Kill]], with a goal to release it for winter 2014. Whilst initially having the funds for a twenty minute episode, Trigger launched a [[Kickstarter]] campaign to extend its runtime by fifteen minutes. The Kickstarter was launched on July 9, 2013 and met its $150,000 goal within five hours. A stretch goal of $500,000 was added to produce a making of documentary and audio commentary for the Bluray release. The Kickstarter raised a total of $625,518. Ootsuka has stated that if the sequel performs well, they may potentially look into producing a television series or full length film. A television series was eventually made for the series in Winter 2017, and was premiered on Netflix.

Alternate identity of [[Kirisame Marisa]] in the Scarlet Devil Tower incident of [[Touhou LostWord]]. Until the Lost Word Incident in her world is resolved, Marisa is not present and an alternate personality is in control.

Some traits are important to keep in mind when determining if the character is the Witch of Scarlet Dreams, or just Marisa in red. First, her black hat and dress have turned red, her white hat ribbon has turned black, and her clothes are more damaged than normal. If these facts are missing, she's likely just Marisa wearing red. Next, her broom is thicker and looks like more than one broomstick twisted together like thin trees. If her broom is present and it's not in this thicker form, assume she's not the Witch of Scarlet Dreams unless otherwise indicated by the artist. Ignore this detail if the broom is not present.

title: forbidden_city
body:
The Forbidden City is a palace complex in Dongcheng District, [[Beijing]], [[China]], at the center of the Imperial City of Beijing. It is surrounded by numerous opulent imperial gardens and temples including Zhongshan Park, the sacrificial Imperial Ancestral Temple, Beihai Park, and the Jingshan Park. It includes the Palace Museum containing parts of the former Imperial art collection.

The Forbidden City was constructed from 1406 to 1420, and was the former Chinese imperial palace and winter residence of the Emperor of China from the Ming dynasty (since the Yongle Emperor) to the end of the Qing dynasty, between 1420 and 1924. The Forbidden City served as the home of Chinese emperors and their households and was the ceremonial and political center of the Chinese government for over 500 years. Since 1925, the Forbidden City has been under the charge of the Palace Museum, whose extensive collection of artwork and artifacts were built upon the imperial collections of the Ming and Qing dynasties. The Forbidden City was declared a World Heritage Site in 1987.

title: m3_lee
body:
The Medium Tank M3 was an American [[tank]] used during [[World War II]]. Design commenced in July 1940, and the first M3s were operational in late 1941. The U.S. Army needed a medium tank armed with a 75 mm gun, and coupled with the United Kingdom's demand for 3,650 medium tanks immediately, the Lee began production by late 1940.

The tank's peculiar design of outfitting the main 75 mm gun in a casemate on the left side of the hull, as well as a fully traversable turret with 37 mm gun, was a compromise meant to produce a tank as soon as possible while the [[M4 Sherman]] is still under development.

title: pangya
body:
An online multiplayer [[golf]] game series. The original game was launched in South Korea in 2004, North America and Japan in 2005, and Thailand in 2007. Only the Thai version of the original game remains online as of 2020, with the Korean and North American servers having closed in 2016 and in Japan in 2017.

Tomy released a single player version, [b]Pangya: Fantasy Golf[/b], in 2009.

The iOS and Android successor title [b]Pangya Mobile[/b] was launched in all four regions in 2017, before closing in 2020. A revised version, [b]Pangya M[/b], was launched on July 3, 2020 for mobile devices alongside a PC version on the NCSoft Purple platform.

title: milk_inside_a_bag_of_milk_inside_a_bag_of_milk
body:
Milk Inside a Bag of Milk Inside a Bag of Milk (stylized as Milk inside a bag of milk inside a bag of milk...) is a 2020 horror visual novel game developed by Russian game developer Nikita Kryukov.

The game centers around an unnamed female protagonist (named [[Milk-chan (milk series)|]] by fans) who visits a nearby grocery market to purchase a bag of milk, but is troubled with the challenges of suffering from severe trauma and psychosis. The player plays as a voice inside her head with which she shares an inner monologue. 

Received a sequel in 2021, entitled "Milk outside a bag of milk outside a bag of milk", colloquially referred to as [i]"Milk 2"[/i] by fans. The sequel shows Milk-chan's character, as the first game takes place mostly from a first person perspective.

title: astrid_(fire_emblem)
body:
[b]Astrid[/b] (ステラ [i]sutera[/i]; Stella) is a playable character from [[Fire Emblem: Path of Radiance]] and [[Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn]].

She is a member of the Crimean Royal Knights, and a former member of Begnion's noble House Damiel. Astrid was engaged to Duke [[Lekain]] of Gaddos, a sinister man and the main antagonist of Fire Emblem: Radiant Dawn, against her wishes. In order to avoid being put through such misery, she left home to seek her fortunes elsewhere. In [i]Path of Radiance[/i], she is also able to befriend [[Sothe (Fire Emblem)|]], [[Gatrie (Fire Emblem)|]] or [[Makalov (Fire Emblem)|]] via supports, the latter of whom she is infamous for giving undeserved praise in [i]Radiant Dawn[/i].

[b]Starting Class[/b]: Bow Knight (Path of Radiance), Bow Paladin (Radiant Dawn).

She has [[long hair|long]], [[black hair]] and [[amber eyes]], and wears a white [[breastplate]] with [[shoulder pads]] and a [[purple shirt]]. Notably, she bears a strong resemblance to [[Ayra (Fire Emblem)|]], except for different eye colors and armor designs.

title: seibetsu_"mona_lisa"_no_kimi_e
body:
Seibetsu "Mona Lisa" no Kimi e (性別「モナリザ」の君へ, En: The Gender of Mona Lisa) is a 2018-to-2022 coming-of-age romance drama manga by Yoshimura Tsumuji.  The manga uses [[spot color]] in otherwise regular [[monochrome]] illustrations.

The story follows high schooler senior [[Arima Hinase]] along with their two childhood friends Takayama Shiori and Kaga Ritsu.  In a world where people are genderless until they reach the age of 12 and then become male or female based upon their gender preference, Hinase has reached the eighteenth spring of their life still remaining genderless.  Feeling their time together is running out, Hinase's female friend Ritsu and male friend Shiori both confess their love each desiring the push Hinase to be a boy or girl.  This leaves Hinase confused, scared, and struggling to really understand themself.  Given the reaction this has caused from Hinase, this also makes Shiori and Ritsu question themselves and what they really want with their relation to Hinase.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: The Gender of Mona Lisa":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Gender_of_Mona_Lisa]

title: apex_legends
body:
Free-to-play battle-royale game released by [[Respawn Entertainment]] in February 2019 for [[Xbox One]], [[PlayStation 4]], and [[computer|PC]], with a [[Nintendo Switch]] port in 2021 and an upgraded version for [[Xbox Series X]] and [[PlayStation 5]] in 2022. A [[apex legends mobile|smartphone port]] developed in collaboration with Tencent's LightSpeed Studios was released in 2022, though it ultimately shut down in 2023. The port was treated as a separate game entirely and featured exclusive cosmetics and legends.

It quickly gained mass popularity, rivaling contemporaries such as [[Overwatch]], [[Playerunknown's Battlegrounds|PUBG]] & [[Fortnite]] in player & streaming view count. The game is notably very popular in Japan, where first-person shooters typically have difficulty finding a large following. It is the favorite game of many [[virtual YouTuber]]s and eSports players, with both [[Hololive]]/[[Holostars]] and [[Nijisanji]] having several talents who dedicate most of their stream time to playing it.

Despite not featuring the parkour and mecha elements of the main series, Apex Legends is considered a canon part of the [[Titanfall (series)|]] franchise. Due to how it's largely treated as a separate entity with its own spin-offs, the Titanfall series tag should not be added to Apex posts unless there's a direct reference beyond the shared weapons.

title: kazami_yuuka
body:
The "Flower Master of the Four Seasons".

Final Boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Lotus Land Story]][/i] and later a recurring playable character, as well as the fourth [[Kazami Yuuka (PC-98)|PC-98]] generation character after [[Hakurei Reimu]], [[Kirisame Marisa]] and [[Alice Margatroid]] to reappear in the Windows generation (specifically in [i][[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]][/i]).

A highly dangerous youkai with the power to manipulate [[flower]]s, and reputed creator and original wielder of the [[Master Spark]] (which Marisa later "borrowed"). Hinted by [[Hieda no Akyuu]] to exhibit a rather polite facade, provided she or her flowers are not harmed. Once described by ZUN as "Youkai moe~", possibly meant as a pun given that the literal meaning of moe is "budding" and Yuuka controls flowers. Yuuka's place of residence is unknown in canon, but is generally assumed to be the [[Garden of the Sun]], where she tends a [[flower field|massive field]] of [[sunflower]]s, and it is known she used to occupy the Dream World mansion [[Mugenkan]] with her then-retainer [[Elly (touhou)|]]. Frequently portrayed in fan works as the [[sadism|Ultimate Sadistic Creature]] (USC), as a bloodthirsty psychopath, or as tsundere.  Usually some combination of the first two (or of all three).  Alternately, she is often depicted as lonely due to this reputation or as very friendly to [[Team 9 (touhou)|]] and other children.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] with [[medium bangs|medium-length bangs]] and [[red eyes]], sometimes [[yellow eyes|yellow]]. Her outfit consists of an [[open vest|open]] [[plaid vest|plaid]] [[red vest]] over a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] tied with a [[yellow ascot]]. To complete her [[skirt set]] is a matching [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[red skirt]] with [[frilled skirt|frills]] or [[plaid pants|plaid]] [[red pants]]. Her footwear is usually [[white socks]] with [[red footwear|red]] [[mary janes]] or [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]]. She usually carries her [[pink umbrella|pink]] [[parasol]].

h4. Fan-made Variations

* "Noukarin":[http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%81%AE%E3%81%86%E3%81%8B%E3%82%8A%E3%82%93] (Farmer-Yuukarin): Originally a type of [[Yukkuri Shiteitte Ne]], unusually depicted with a full body instead of just as a head.  Now this word means Kazami Yuuka wearing a [[straw hat]].  Noukarin is frequently depicted with an acoustic [[guitar]] and/or with an almost impenetrable rural accent. 
* "Bakerin":[http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%81%B9%E3%83%BC%E3%81%8B%E3%82%8A%E3%82%93] (Bakery-Yuukarin): A recent variant of Kazami Yuuka who makes [[bread]] in her own bakery named "[[Bakery]] Kazami".  "A certain tweet":http://twitter.com/matsurisyndrome/status/51104783376990208 caused this trend.

title: hastings_kamuzu_banda
body:
The leader of [[Malawi]] from 1961 to 1994.

 After receiving much of his education overseas, Banda returned to his home country (then British Nyasaland) to speak against colonialism and advocate independence. In 1963 he was formally appointed prime minister of Nyasaland and, a year later, led the country to independence as Malawi. Two years later he proclaimed Malawi a republic with himself as president. He consolidated power and later declared Malawi a one-party state under the [[Malawi Congress Party]] (MCP). In 1970 the MCP made him the party's President for Life. In 1971 he became President for Life of Malawi itself.

As a leader of the pro-Western bloc in Africa he received support from the West during the [[Cold War]]. He generally supported women's rights, improved the country's infrastructure and maintained a good educational system relative to other African countries but also presided over one of the most repressive regimes in Africa. His government regularly tortured and murdered political opponents. Human rights groups estimate that at least 6,000 people were killed, tortured and jailed without trial. As many as 18,000 people were killed during his rule according to one estimate. He was scorned for maintaining full diplomatic relations with apartheid-era [[South Africa]].

By 1993 he was facing international pressure and widespread protest. A referendum ended his one-party state and a special assembly ended his life-term presidency, stripping him of most of his powers. Banda ran for president in the democratic elections which followed and was defeated. He died in South Africa in 1997.

title: destroyer_(eve_online)
body:
A type of [[spacecraft|spaceships]] from the [[EVE Online]].
Destructive, albeit fragile craft meant as anti-frigate platforms.

Destroyers are larger ships than [[frigate (EVE Online)|]]s, but they still mount the same small-sized modules that frigates use. The Tech 1 destroyers have a large number of high slots, giving them a lot of firepower for their size and cost and making them good at salvaging. The [[Tech 2 ship (EVE Online)|Tech 2]] destroyers have unique abilities: [[Interdictor]]s can launch warp disruption probes in nullsec and wormholes to prevent groups of enemy ships from warping away, and Command Destroyers can provide link boosts and utilize Micro Jump Field Generators to move nearby ships 100 km away. [[Tactical destroyer (EVE Online)|]]s, the [[Tech 3 ship (EVE Online)|Tech 3]] destroyers, have exceptional flexibility and firepower.

h5. External links: 
https://universe.eveonline.com/lore/destroyers
https://wiki.eveuniversity.org/Destroyers

title: frigate_(eve_online)
body:
A type of [[spacecraft|spaceships]] from the [[EVE Online]].
Small, fast but fragile vessels suited to a variety of purposes, especially tackling.

Frigates are the smallest and fastest ships in EVE. New pilots begin by flying frigates, and the Tech 1 frigates only cost a few hundred thousand ISK. Don't be fooled by the low cost of frigates and the fact that they're used by novice pilots, though: frigates can play an important role in battle, and in numbers or with skilled pilots even Tech 1 frigates can be deadly.
There are a number of classes of [[Tech 2 ship (EVE Online)|Tech 2]] frigates, which have advanced abilities and are also much more focused on a particular role: tackling [[interceptor (EVE Online)|]]s, cloaking and scanning covert ops frigates, surprise-attack stealth bombers, [[electronic warfare ship (EVE Online)|electronic attack]] frigates for electronic warfare, and [[Assault ship (EVE Online)|assault]] frigates, which are designed purely to deal and survive damage.

h5. External links: 
https://universe.eveonline.com/lore/frigates
https://wiki.eveuniversity.org/Frigates
